author: Russell Brand
description:
Rand Paul lays out why distrust in government is not only justified—it’s necessary. From the COVID cover-up to the Epstein case, he reveals how powerful interests across agencies protect themselves, hide evidence, and punish dissenters. When FOIA lawsuits work better than Congressional subpoenas, and elites walk free while ordinary people face decades in prison, what does that say about the system? This isn’t about conspiracy—it’s about convergence.
